# Developer Portfolio Architecture

A custom, high-fidelity, responsive multi-page portfolio website built to showcase my professional journey, technical projects, SEO work, and evolving focus toward ELK Stack and AI integration engineering.

## 🛠️ Technology & Structural Stack
- **Frontend Core**: Vanilla HTML5 and semantic CSS3 layout structures.
- **Typography & Font Framework**: Syne, Inter, and JetBrains Mono via Google Fonts.
- **Navigation & View Routing**: Custom state-routing logic in `main.js` for page switching, deep links, hash history, and mobile interactions.
- **Animation System**: CSS animations and JavaScript-driven viewport interactions for smooth transitions and visual polish.

## 📂 Repository File Blueprint
```text
├── css/
│   ├── style.css
│   ├── animations.css
│   └── responsive.css
├── js/
│   └── main.js
├── assets/
│   └── Arun_Agarwal.png
└── index.html
```

## 🚀 Environment Optimization & SEO Best Practices
- **Image Strategy**: Use compressed, descriptive images with proper alt text.
- **Font Delivery**: Preconnect Google Fonts for faster loading and reduced layout shift.
- **Inline Vectors**: Use SVG icons directly in the markup for better performance and scalability.

## ✨ Project Overview
This portfolio is designed as a guided digital experience rather than a static resume. It presents my background in SEO, content architecture, technical audits, platform building, ELK Stack work, and backend learning in a structured and interactive format.

The site uses a custom front-end architecture where JavaScript controls active page state, navigation transitions, mobile menu behavior, and idle auto-navigation. This keeps the experience lightweight, smooth, and easy to maintain.

## 🔧 Architecture Notes
The project is organized around a simple but deliberate structure:

- `index.html` holds the full page markup and content sections.
- `main.js` manages page routing, swipe gestures, keyboard navigation, history hashes, and form actions.
- CSS files handle layout, responsiveness, animations, and visual consistency.
- Assets are stored separately to keep the project organized and easy to deploy.

Instead of relying on a heavy framework, the site uses vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to keep performance high and dependency count low. The layout is built to feel modern while still being practical for long-term maintenance.

## 📱 Responsive Behavior
The website is built to adapt across desktop and mobile screens. Navigation, hero sections, content blocks, and interactive elements are designed to reflow cleanly on smaller devices. The mobile experience also includes gesture support and page-state syncing.

